      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this function,\"texture life time as a resource\" seems being maintained in two places; at the higher level, in the renderer with the cached texture objects, and at the level of individual scene objects that also hold references.\n\nTexture life time changes also happen in a special way for posters; when set set the texture of a poster from the UI or wherever, the poster object itself triggers the releasing of the previous texture (which is also the apparent reason for this function to depend on sceneObject).\n\nTo reduce specialness, and maybe simplify things, might we instead release the previous texture from the Scene itself by doing something like mRenderer.releaseTexture(texture) in Scene.cpp\u0027s loadPoster function?\n\nIn the long run (this can be another CL), let\u0027s consider the idea of not organizing textures, meshes, and materials per scene object, and instead have global vectors for each resource type, and a global refcount for each one. On scene object addition or removal, Renderer or Scene would explicit increment or decrement the refcount.",
