      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve also been thinking more about the vector of textures in SceneObjectData serving as a refcount, and comparing its use against the mTextureCache, and I was wondering, could we forgo the vector of textures per scene object? That seemed good at the time, but I now see that it could induce quite some complexity / coupling.\n\nThe benefit of just having one place to modify when releasing textures is that releaseTexture doesn\u0027t need to depend on the sceneObject; together with the comment above, we can continue to have the object resource release calls that occur during normal scene lifetime (not tearing down the whole thing) mostly triggered from Scene.cpp.",
